<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-05-23T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-05-23T17:00:00-05:00" n="279" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d279">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3141: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Feely</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">La
                                    Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-23T18:00:00-04:00">May 23, 1933—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>53. The Bolivian Government today instructed its Ministers in the four
                            neighboring countries to urge prompt acceptance of the invitation to
                            join with the Neutral Commission in the renewal of negotiations for a
                            peaceful settlement.</p>
                        <p>The British and French Ministers here today received instructions to urge
                            Bolivia to accept the League formula.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Feely</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>